{
  "stem": "22869.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He would line up the people in the morning, take something that is common here in America, called maybe a baseball bat, and slug any kind of a person that he felt like it two times on the neck, one times on the back, and bingo.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The man was dead.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he had to give no accounting to anybody as long he produced a dead body.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I mean, to watch these atrocities-- this dehumanizing of-- of day in and day out, this lack of-- of food-- I came to a point where watching a person die meant nothing.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It's like watching a fly go by today.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It probably hurts me more today when a fly dies than it hurt me at that time a human being dying.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was so common.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was-- it was in such multiples, and you saw it minute in and minute out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We were going, I remember, the three brothers-- there was-- there was nothing left on us as far as weight.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I mean, we were all bones.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And at one time or another, we were all weak.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We were all-- we couldn't walk.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But we were like holding onto each other, one trying to give a little bit-- drag to the other one, so we can continue walking.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Because we knew the minute you let yourself go, and you're on the ground, you're out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was a battle.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember standing in a camp in the morning by appelle.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When you count people, when you dish out the food, the abuse was constant.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Summer with the heat and winter with the cold, no protection whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if somebody was missing, or the count wasn't right, you could stand there for hours.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
